Brevan Howard Cuts Management Fee for Listed Macro Hedge Fund - Bloomberg






























































  
















Brevan Howard Cuts Management Fee for Listed Macro Hedge Fund
By Nishant Kumar
        
@nishantkumar07
More stories by Nishant Kumar





October 19, 2016, 9:56 AM EDT








Brevan Howard Capital Management LP won’t charge a management fee on profits generated by BH Macro Ltd., a listed fund that invests in the main hedge fund run by the firm.The policy came into effect on Oct. 3, Brevan Howard said in a filing on Wednesday. The new arrangement will also result in Brevan Howard Master Fund Ltd. waiving an operational services fee charged on gains from the BH Macro fund.A company spokesman declined to comment.




Brevan, run by billionaire Alan Howard, is contending with investor withdrawals amid losses this year. The firm stopped charging management fees on new investments by existing clients in the master fund and a $1.8 billion multistrategy fund, a person with knowledge of the matter said last month.Brevan Howard Master Fund, down 3.4 percent in 2016, managed $13.7 billion at the end of September, according to investor letters. That’s down from as much as $27 billion in 2014.



Before it's here, it's on the Bloomberg Terminal.

